  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Obstructed Defecation is a profoundly disabling condition. Many different surgical procedures
      has been introduced to treat patients affected by this disease. The most used are STARR and
      ventral rectopexy. Because of the heterogenity of studies and overall the lack of comparison
      trials, there is no accepted standard surgical treatment.PRO-REST aimed to compare these two
      procedures (STARR and Ventral Rectopexy) evaluating functional and anatomical results.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
